## Advanced Remixing Techniques

AceStep1.5

This workflow is a highly custom example of remixing an input song into something totally new. We use features to control what happens, where, how much, and for how long. Musical intuition is involved here.

## Features

We use features and combine them iteratively to remix the input song. Iteratively means that I generate output, then circle back and edit these features. 


### Think of features as a timeline. 

There are dozens of feature sources - we use 'time feature' here, but theres audio, midi, color, depth, pitch, whisper, brightness....you get the idea.  

Likewise, there are many dozens of nodes that allow you to combine and manipulate these features. Here, we use the advanced feature combiner to shape exactly what we want. This was an iterative process.
